<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880505-0009 </DOCNO><HL> Britain's Official Reserves Rise </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EUROP </CO><IN> MON </IN><DATELINE> LONDON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Britain's official reserves, mainly gold and convertible foreign currencies, increased an underlying $514 million in April from March, the Treasury said.    The underlying figure takes into account official repayments and new borrowings. Before such transactions were included, the reserves showed a rise of $338 million from March, to a record $47.86 billion. </TEXT></DOC>